result.execSummary:
The defendant Tromance K Washington was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Child Abuse-Intentionally Cause Harm, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.03(2)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Tromance K Washington in court with attorney Paul Garland Bonneson.  Defendant Tromance K Washington in custody.  Molly M Schmidt appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
cab
Defendant informs the court that he wants to change his plea.
Plea hearing proceeded...
.
As to Count 1:
On motion of the state, the penalty enhancer, "repeater" is dismissed.
As to charge as amended:
  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information, as amended, and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.
. The parties want to proceed to sentencing..
.
As to count 1:
   Sentencing proceeds. Statements made by the State, defense counsel and defendant.
Court sentenced defendant to serve a term of IMPRISONMENT in the Wisconsin State Prisons for 4 YEARS. INITIAL CONFINEMENT of 2 YEARS and EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 2 YEARS. Credit given for 92 days time served if revoked.
.
COURT STAYS sentence and places defendant on PROBATION for 18 MONTHS.
.
CONDITIONS OF PROBATION/EXTENDED SUPERVISION: 
-Any counseling the agent feels is appropriate.
-Parenting Classes.
-Anger Management.
- No physical punishment of childen.
--Defendant to pay all applicable costs and surcharges, victim/witness surcharge, the domestic violence surcharge, and supervision fees as determined by the Department of Corrections.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.
-Defendant to pay all supervision fees as determined by the Department of Corrections.

.As to count 2:
On motion of the state and pursuant to negotiations, court ordered count 2 dismissed and read-in for sentencing.
Jury trial date of 10/07/15 vacated.

Ineligible Voting Notice.
  Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm.
